# {{n-g|Particle indicating the word preceding it is used as an adverb.}}
#: {{zh-x|很 快 地{de}|very quick'''ly'''}}
#: {{zh-x|佢 偷偷 地{dei6-2} 走 咗 喇。|He secret'''ly''' left.|C}}
#* {{zh-x|你 乖 乖 地{dei6-2} 坐 喺度 喇 吓。|Sit here and behave, ok?|C}}
#: {{zh-alt-inline|{{l|zh|的}}, {{l|zh|底}} ''obsolete''|c=1}}

* The use of this particle is always optional after polysyllabic adverbs.
*: {{zh-x|非常 短|very short}}
*: {{zh-x|非常 地{de} 短|very short}}
* On the contrary, monosyllabic adverbs are compulsorily used with or without {{lang|zh|地}}.
*: {{zh-x|很 漂亮{liang}|very beautiful}} (where *{{lang|zh|很地漂亮}} is unacceptable)
*: {{zh-x|倏 地{de} 不見|to disappear suddenly}} (where *{{lang|zh|倏不見}} is unacceptable in Modern Standard Chinese)
* However, there is an exception:
*: {{zh-x|猛 回頭|to turn the head back suddenly}}
*: {{zh-x|猛 地{de} 回頭|to turn the head back suddenly}}

